frameDefinitions: An Entity survives a situation with some Support, which tends to be far below the accustomed or standard level expected.
The LUs in this frame refer to biological entities other than human beings and plants, which are labeled by the FE Animal.  ''  'My husband and I adopted a really sweet dog last year.'
This frame has to do with people (the Residents) residing in Locations, sometimes with a Co-resident.

This frame concerns an Addict's physiological or psychological compulsive dependence on an Addictant, the substance or behavior to which the Addict is addicted. '' 'Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became hooked on that designer drug instantly.'

The answer to one open question, the Outcome, is dictated (partially or completely) by the answer to another open question, the Determinant, i.e. if the answer to the Determinant is known, the answer to the Outcome can be predicted.
frameExamples: Harry <t>subsisted</t> on ramen and cheap beer through college.
My husband and I adopted a really sweet dog last year.
Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became <t>hooked</t> on that designer drug instantly.
Economic policy is partially a <t>function</t> of cultural values.
listRoleDefinitions: The living organism which requires the <fen>Support</fen> to survive.
The resource that the <fen>Entity</fen> relies on to survive through a situation.
The living organism belonging to the kingdom Animalia.
The individual(s) that reside at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The place in which somebody resides.
A person or group of people that the resident is staying with or among.
This role refers to the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Resident</fen> resides.
The <fen>Addict</fen> is physiologically or psychologically dependent on a substance or a behavior.
<fen>Addictant</fen> is the substance or behavior to which the <fen>Addict</fen> is dependent.
An open question that is (to some degree) predictable from the Determinant.
An open question that determines the <fen>Outcome</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>He</fex> lived on peanuts until she came along.
Harry managed to subsist <fex>on ramen and cheap beer</fex> through college.
Did you see that <fex>bird</fex> in the tree?
Price, in such a case, depends <fex>only on the whim of the supplier</fex>.
